articles.author: JINTAMAS SAKSORNCHAI, ALANNA DURKIN RICHER and ERIC TUCKER
articles.description: BANGKOK (AP) — A plane believed to be carrying WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange has landed in Bangkok on Tuesday, as he is on the way to enter a plea deal with the U.S.
articles.title: WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange stops in Bangkok on his way to a US court and later freedom

articles.author: BY ABBY SEWELL AND MELANIE LIDMAN
articles.description: BEIRUT (AP) — The prospect of a full-scale war between Israel and Lebanon’s Hezbollah militant group terrifies people on both sides of the border, but some see it as an inevitable fallout from Israel’s ongoing war against Hamas in Gaza, particularly as cease-fire negotiations have faltered.
articles.title: With another setback for cease-fire talks, worries of full-scale war for Israel and Lebanon escalate

articles.author: WILL WEISSERT
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — It could be a well-rehearsed zinger or an offhand, too-loud sigh.Notable moments from past presidential debates demonstrate how the candidates' words and body language can make them look especially relatable or hopelessly out-of-touch.
articles.title: How memorable debate moments are made: on the fly, rehearsed — and sometimes without a word uttered

articles.author: RICHARD LARDNER and JACK DURA
articles.description: BISMARCK, N.D. (AP) — North Dakota Gov. Doug Burgum is one of Donald Trump’s most visible and vocal backers, sprinting around the country to drum up support for the former president’s comeback bid while auditioning to be his running mate.
articles.title: A potential Trump VP pick backs a controversial CO2 pipeline favored by the Biden White House

articles.author: JOHN HANNA
articles.description: TOPEKA, Kan. (AP) — Federal judges in Kansas and Missouri on Monday together blocked much of a Biden administration student loan repayment plan that provides a faster path to cancellation and lower monthly payments for millions of borrowers.
articles.title: Missouri, Kansas judges temporarily halt much of President Biden's student debt forgiveness plan

articles.author: RUSS BYNUM and JIM MUSTIAN
articles.description: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) — Julian Lewis didn’t pull over for the Georgia State Patrol cruiser flashing its blue lights behind him on a rural highway. He still didn't stop after pointing a hand out the window and turning onto a darkened dirt road as the trooper sounded his siren.
articles.title: Shot in 1.6 seconds: Video raises questions about how trooper avoided charges in Black man's death

articles.author: MARGERY A. BECK, HANNAH FINGERHUT and JOHN HANNA
articles.description: NORTH SIOUX CITY, S.D. (AP) — More storms are possible in parts of the deluged Midwest, where flooding after days of heavy rains has killed at least two people, sent a river surging around a dam and forced evacuations and rescues.
articles.title: More rain possible in deluged Midwest as flooding kills 2, causes water to surge around dam

articles.author: DASHA LITVINOVA and ERIC TUCKER
articles.description: TALLINN, Estonia (AP) — One was a journalist on a reporting trip. Another was attending a wedding.
articles.title: More Americans are ending up in Russian jails. Prospects for their release are unclear

articles.author: HYUNG-JIN KIM
articles.description: SEOUL, South Korea (AP) — Rescue workers were combing through the charred ruins of a factory building near South Korea's capital to find any more fire victims Tuesday, a day after a devastating blaze likely triggered by exploding lithium batteries killed 22 people, mostly Chinese migrant workers.
articles.title: South Korean rescuers search burned factory after a blaze killed 22, mostly Chinese migrants
